abstract: The top Senate Democrat and Republican negotiating new Wall Street regulation said Wednesday they expect to resolve their differences before the end of January, an optimistic outlook for a bill that had seemed mired in partisan conflicts.

lead_paragraph: The top Senate Democrat and Republican negotiating new Wall Street regulation said Wednesday they expected to resolve their differences before the end of January, an optimistic outlook for a bill that had seemed mired in partisan conflicts, The Associated Press reported.

headline.main: Senators Settle a Wall Street Impasse
